         python3-systemd (>= 235),
         openssh-client,
         iputils-ping
Description: CUEMS power bridge — Shelly + Companion shutdown coordinator
 cuems-power-bridge is the HTTP-fronted coordinator that orchestrates
 orderly cluster shutdown when an operator flips the wired Shelly Pro 1
 power switch, or presses the shutdown button on a Bitfocus Companion
 Stream Deck. It also fronts GO / STOP for Stream Deck operation,
 translating HTTP POSTs into WebSocket-OSC frames against the engine
 on :9190.
 .
 The bridge maintains persistent WebSocket connections to the controller
 engine (:9190, binary OSC) and the editor (:9092, JSON). It refuses
 shutdown while a project is running, SSHes every NodeType.slave from
 /etc/cuems/network_map.xml to power them off, polls until they go
 silent on the network, arms a Shelly hardware safety timer, then
 systemctl-poweroffs the controller — the Shelly cuts mains a configured
 number of seconds later, on an already-off box.
 .
 Auto-loads a configurable show project at boot via the editor's
 project_ready WebSocket action, matching the proven wsclient.py pattern.
 .
 Installs into /usr/lib/cuems/ virtualenv (provided by cuems-utils).
 Console entry points at /usr/lib/cuems/bin/{cuems-power-bridge,
 cuems-power-bridge-deploy-keys,cuems-wsclient}. systemd unit is shipped
 in cuems-common.
